array backwards\n            for j in range(target, num - 1, -1):\n                dp[j] = dp[j] or dp[j - num]\n        \n        return dp[target]\n```\n\nThis solution uses dynamic programming to determine if we can partition the array into two subsets with equal sums. The idea is to use a boolean array `dp` where `dp[i]` indicates whether a subset with sum `i` can be formed from the elements of the array. We iterate through each number in the array and update the `dp` array accordingly. If `dp[target]` is true at the end, it means we can partition the array into two subsets with equal sums.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}